review_blob: Wonderful beer, tastes not as fresh as I would like but still great!  I like almost any Belgian IPA, but this one is special.
beer_name: Hoppin Frog Hop Masters Abbey Belgian-Style Double IPA

review_blob: I really enjoyed this beer.  It wasnt as sour as I expected which was not a huge disappointment as I was wishing for anything really.  It was well balanced and spiced.  It really tasted like a differently spiced witbier, very good!
beer_name: Jolly Pumpkin Project Greenleaf: Hummocky Lick Sumac Sensation

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: What a wonderful beer.  My first beer love was Aventinus so it is no wonder that I loved this concentrated version.  It was everything I dreamed of with less alcohol taste than expected for 12%.  Weizen-bocks are amazing beers.  I would really like to see a barrel aged version...
